==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disorganization
<hw>Dis*or`gan*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧sorganisation</ets>. See <er>Disorganize</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of disorganizing; destruction
of system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being disorganized; <as>as, the
<ex>disorganization</ex> of the body, or of government</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The magazine of a pawnbroker in such total
<qex>disorganization</qex>, that the owner can never lay his hands upon
any one article at the moment he has occasion for it.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disorganize</ent>⟦br⟧
